Product name: Universal Typewriter Ribbon 1/2 Inch Ribbon 2 inch Spools with Expanding Center Core
Description:
PLEASE READ:  IF THE SPOOLS IN YOUR TYPEWRITER MEASURE 2 INCHES IN DIAMETER, THEN THESE WILL FIT PERFECTLY IN YOUR MACHINE.
These dual spool universal typewriter ribbons will fit in almost any typewriter.  The width of the ribbon is 1/2 inch and the diameter across one of the plastic spools is 2 inches.  The hole in the center of each spool is EXPANDABLE, so it will fit all spindle sizes.  The center also pops out to make room for very large spindles.  TYPEWRITER RIBBONS FROM OTHER, CHEAPER SHOPS DON'T HAVE THIS FEATURE.  If for some reason these spools do not fit in your typewriter, simply rewind the ribbon onto your old spools and voilà!
We sell ribbons in three styles: solid black, half black and half red, & half black and half white cover-up tape.   Unfortunately, we are temporarily sold out of Black and White. Be sure to check out our vibrantly colored ribbons.  We have highly pigmented ribbons in red, orange, green, blue, purple, and pink!
These typewriter ribbon are made fresh every couple days to ensure you are getting the best product available!  We care about you and want to answer any questions and address any concerns you may have.  We want to share the joy of typewriters with you!
If you are unsure if these ribbons will work in your typewriter, please let us know the model of your typewriter and we will confirm that these ribbons will work for you, or point you in the right direction if they do not.  
We ship your typewriter ribbons the day after your payment is received via USPS first class mail.  If possible, we ship the same day! We will supply you with your package's tracking number once we ship it.

 ❤TUTORIAL ❤
 ❤CABOCHON PENDANT ❤
For making a simple cabochon pendant, you will need the following:
- Clear glass cabochon
- Cabochon Tray
- Gloss Glaze
- E-6000 Adhesive
- Graphic or photo
1. Choose and cut out an image that fits the cabochon tray.
2. Squeeze a thin coat of glaze on to back of the glass.
3. Place the image face down onto the back of the glass and press firmly to remove any air bubbles. Set the tile aside and allow it to dry completely.
4. Squeeze a dab of E-6000 adhesive to the back of the image, spread it evenly and place it inside of the cabochon tray. Press firmly.
5. Allow it to dry completely and your pendant is ready to wear!!
